  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      One paraffin block is routinely used for Human Epidermal Growth Factor Receptor 2 (Her2/neu)
      immunohistochemistry (IHC) assessment. Here, investigators investigated if picking two or
      multiple paraffin blocks for Her2/neu evaluation is an economical, efficient and practical
      method, which may reduce false-negativity of Her2/neu IHC assessment due to intratumoral
      heterogeneity.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
